        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 3:02PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mesita, or 24 miles southeast of San Luis Valley Airport, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Luis, San Acacio, Mesita, San Pablo, and Sanchez Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
